---
// A small cue shown on links that open in a new browser tab: a muted "leaves the
// site" glyph for sighted readers, plus text only a screen reader hears, so a new
// tab is never a surprise. Rendered next to outbound links only, from
// CountryBriefing.astro, which decides when a link is outbound.
---
<span class="nt">
  <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V8a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h6"/><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"/><line x1="10" y1="14" x2="21" y2="3"/></svg>
  <span class="nt-sr">(opens in a new tab)</span>
</span>
<style>
  .nt{ display:inline-flex; align-items:center; color:var(--muted); }
  .nt svg{ display:block; }
  .nt-sr{ position:absolute; width:1px; height:1px; padding:0; margin:-1px; overflow:hidden; clip:rect(0 0 0 0); white-space:nowrap; border:0; }
</style>
